                <p>The <strong>Eiffel Tower</strong> is a wrought-iron tower that
                    stands 1,063 ft (324 m) tall in <strong>Paris</strong>.</p>

                <p>Currently, the Eiffel Tower is the most-visited monument
                    in the world with over 7 million visitors a year.</p>
                
                <p>Visitors can choose to go up using the Tower lift or
                    the stairs. There are 1,665 steps to the top.</p>
